# Playground — local environment (template). Copy this to ".env.local" HERE
# (application/playground/) and fill in your values:
#
#   cp .env.local.example .env.local
#
# .env.local is gitignored, so your key and any machine-specific paths stay
# local and never reach git. It is auto-loaded into the server process by
# run_demo.sh and run_dev.sh / run_real.sh.

# --- Required for real chatbot/application turns -----------------------------
# Browsing the catalog works without this; producing real chatbot turns needs a
# valid OpenAI key for RecAI and finance application models.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here

# --- Required when using Claude persona models -------------------------------
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# --- DashScope (Qwen / DeepSeek via OpenAI-compatible API) -------------------
# Required when selecting dashscope/* persona models in Cockpit.
# Get a key from Alibaba Cloud Model Studio (international: ap-southeast-1).
# DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=sk-your-dashscope-key-here
# Optional override for the compatible-mode base URL:
# DASHSCOPE_API_BASE=https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1

# Optional. Defaults to anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5.
# MATRIX_PERSONA_MODEL=anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5
# MATRIX_PERSONA_MODEL=anthropic/claude-opus-4-8
# MATRIX_PERSONA_MODEL=openai/gpt-4o-mini
# MATRIX_PERSONA_MODEL=dashscope/qwen3.6-plus-2026-04-02
# MATRIX_PERSONA_MODEL=dashscope/deepseek-v4-pro

# --- CLI harness subscription auth (optional) --------------------------------
# Default for persona-claude-code / persona-codex / persona-gemini-cli is API
# keys above. To use your local CLI subscription instead, prepare credentials on
# THIS machine (the Harbor runner), then uncomment the matching block below.
# Restart the Playground backend after editing .env.local.
# Details: application/choosing-an-agent.md § CLI subscription auth
#
# Codex (persona-codex): log in once on the host, then enable auth.json injection
#   codex login    # creates ~/.codex/auth.json
# CODEX_FORCE_AUTH_JSON=1
# CODEX_AUTH_JSON_PATH=/absolute/path/to/auth.json   # optional; default ~/.codex/auth.json
#
# Claude Code (persona-claude-code): subscription token from the Claude CLI
#   claude setup-token
# CLAUDE_FORCE_OAUTH=1
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=your-token-here
#
# Gemini CLI (persona-gemini-cli): log in with the Gemini CLI on the host
#   gemini auth login    # creates ~/.gemini/oauth_creds.json (CLI version dependent)
# GEMINI_FORCE_OAUTH=1
# GEMINI_OAUTH_CREDS_PATH=/absolute/path/to/oauth_creds.json   # optional

# --- Optional chatbot sidecar routing ---------------------------------------
# RecAI runs through the local RecAI / InteRecAgent bridge. Finance and medical
# runs call an HTTP chatbot sidecar that implements the shared /v1 chat
# contract. If you expose the shared chatbot router on your host, point
# Playground at it:
# CHATBOT_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000
#
# To bypass the shared router, point each application at its own sidecar:
# CHATBOT_UPSTREAM_FINANCE=http://127.0.0.1:8901
# CHATBOT_UPSTREAM_MEDICAL=http://127.0.0.1:8902
#
# Sidecar-internal settings used by finance / Multi-Agent-Medical-Assistant:
# OPENBB_MCP_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8001/mcp
# MEDICAL_ASSISTANT_URL=http://multi-agent-medical-assistant:8000

# --- Optional: redirect the model caches -------------------------------------
# HuggingFace / sentence-transformers caches default to ~/.cache. On the first
# REAL run, sentence-transformers downloads thenlper/gte-base (~833 MB) there.
# If your home dir is space-constrained, point the caches at a bigger disk by
# uncommenting and editing these (see README.md):
# HF_HOME=/path/to/disk/.cache/huggingface
# TRANSFORMERS_CACHE=/path/to/disk/.cache/huggingface/hub
# SENTENCE_TRANSFORMERS_HOME=/path/to/disk/.cache/torch/sentence_transformers
